title: Great American Railroad Journeys 14of15 Manassas to Richmond 720

Great American Railroad Journeys

Travel Documentary hosted by Michael Portillo, published by BBC in 2016 - English narration 
http://docuwiki.net/images/f/fb/Great-American-Railroad-Journeys-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------

Great American Railroad Journeys
Michael Portillo crosses the Atlantic to ride the railroads of America, armed with Appleton's General Guide to the United States, published in 1879.



14)  Manassas to Richmond 
Michael Portillo arrives in Manassas, scene of not one, but two, crucial battles during the American Civil War, and the first railroad battles in US history. In Fredericksburg, Virginia, he tries his hand at bottling bourbon corn whisky and learns how it became the nation's spirit. In Richmond, a plate of ham and eggs with southern grits sets Michael up for a tour of the Virginia State Capitol building, where he learns about the terrible dilemma faced by one of its most famous sons, General Robert E Lee.
